-Gotha-Altenburg, and Prince August. Nearly three-quarters of the letters are addressed to Charlotte von Stein, his most important correspondent.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aBriefsammlung. 4aGoethe, Johann Wolfgang von. 4aKlassik. 4aRomantik. 4aWeimar.1 aCanal, Héctor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRichter, Elke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZschiedrich, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978311067138440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311067147640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110671476423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110671476/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020